CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 3, 1953, pg. 2, reads: "Outstanding Courier Newsboys - Sub-distributors, under Leroy Randall, Courier distributor in Pittsburgh district, are shown presenting prizes to the tow lads judged 'outstanding newsboys of 1952' who sell papers for them, at the Courier newsboys' party at the Kay Boys' Club last Saturday night. James O. Dougan is shown with the prize won by Sam Ayers, who sells in the East Liberty - Homewood district, and George Jenkins who sells in Monongahela City, is shown with Lloyd Tobias. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Courier newsboys Sam Ayers and George Jenkins receiving prizes from James O. Dougan and Lloyd Tobias, in Kay Boys Club
